HEADWORD: Transfrete
<hw>Trans*frete"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transfretare</ets>; <ets>trans</ets> across, over +
<ets>fretum</ets> a strait: cf. OF. <ets>transfreter</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To pass over a strait or narrow sea.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>transfreight</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>E.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
